<title>UK: Bass shares flat in wake of Allied deal.</title>
<headline>Bass shares flat in wake of Allied deal.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-08-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in brewer Bass Plc were down one penny to 841p at 0745 GMT on Tuesday in the first London trading session since the firm announced a deal on Sunday that saw it buy Allied Domecq's 50 percent stake in Carlsberg-Tetley.</p>
<p>Analysts said the deal, which had been heavily speculated on during the past few months, contained few surprises and had already been calculated into the firm's share price.</p>
<p>&quot;The deal was pretty well signalled,&quot; said one analyst who declined to be named.</p>
